## [**OffSec's Exploit Database Archive**](https://www.exploit-db.com/exploits/49933?source=post_page-----6beb3a173c13---------------------------------------)

### [PHP 8.1.0-dev \- 'User-Agentt' Remote Code Execution.. webapps exploit for PHP platform](https://www.exploit-db.com/exploits/49933?source=post_page-----6beb3a173c13---------------------------------------)

[www.exploit-db.com](https://www.exploit-db.com/exploits/49933?source=post_page-----6beb3a173c13---------------------------------------)

It’s a Remote Code Execution (RCE) exploit that abuses the insecure User-Agent header handling in this PHP dev server.

Then back to our terminal we create an empty file and copy the exploit and paste it there

![][image8]

***nano agenttexp.py***

Before you can run it, you need to give it **execute permission**

***chmod \+x agenttexp.py***

The chmod makes the file **executable**, allowing you to run it like a program or script.

Now we try this :

***pwd***  
***ls \-la***

Nothing useful in the current directory.

So we explore the root directory:

Press enter or click to view image in full size

![][image11]

***ls /***

and flag.txt catches my eyes

Now you may wonder why ls/ ?

* ls \-la lists files in your **current directory** only.  
* ls / shows the **top-level directory** structure — i.e., files and folders in /, the root.

Unless you’re already in /, you won’t see flag.txt with ls \-la

Once we know the flag is in /, we use

Press enter or click to view image in full size
